 8061:                          ;*
 8062:                          ;* Four new I2C communication commands a
 8063:                          ;*
 8064:                          ;* The syntax to use is:
 8065:                          ;*
 8066:                          ;*     I2CSTART           Sends a start 
 8067:                          ;*                        - Returns with
 8068:                          ;*     I2CSTOP            Sends a stop c
 8069:                          ;*                        - Returns with
 8070:                          ;*     I2CPUT [byte]      Sends a byte t
 8071:                          ;*                        - Returns with
 8072:                          ;*     I2CGET [variable]  Reads a byte f
 8073:                          ;*                        - Set 18H (sta
 8074:                          ;*                           DBY(18H) = 
 8075:                          ;*                        - Returns with
 8076:                          ;*   
 8077:                          ;* Register 18H is the I2C communication
 8078:                          ;*
 8079:                          ;*     STATUS=DBY(18H)
 8080:                          ;*      IF STATUS.AND.2=2 PRINT "Time ou
 8081:                          ;*      IF STATUS.AND.4=4 PRINT "Busy er
 8082:                          ;*      IF STATUS.AND.8=8 PRINT "No ackn
 8083:                          ;*
 8084:                          ;*--------------------------------------
 8085:                          ;*
 8086:                          ;* Two new commands to read from or writ
 8087:                          ;*
